🥔 Accordion Potatoes 📝 Recipe 1-2 Potato Water 1 tsp • Salt 1 tsp • Baking Soda Oil Dried Parsley Chili Sauce Steps: • Cutting the Potato - Peel off the potato - Cut the ends of potato - Cut the potato lengthwise / just like shown in my video, however you like and based on the size of the potato - Take 2 skewers - Put the potato horizontally and place the skewers on both sides of the potato - Cut the potato in vertical lines - Flip the potato - Cut the potato again in diagonal lines • Soaking; Accordion Potatoes - Prepare water with salt and baking soda - Soak the accordion potatoes in water for 5-10 minutes - After soaking the potatoes, dry them with tissue / towel • Cooking; Accordion Potatoes - Heat the oil in pan at medium heat - Fry the accordion potatoes until crispy and golden brown • Finishing; Accordion Potatoes - Serve the potato with dried parsley and chili sauce Tips: 1. After cutting the potato into accordion shape, you will slice another ones. So keep the potato that have already been cut in water to prevent the potato turning into brown color.
